ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Proactive Parenting Score
Notes: Mean of items: 15, 19, 28, 32, 33, and 34

ElementDescription: Positive Reinforcement Score
Notes: Mean of items: 11, 18, 26, and 30

ElementDescription: Warmth Score
Notes: Mean of items: 1, 7, and 21

ElementDescription: Supportiveness Score
Notes: Mean of items: 10, 17, and 22

ElementDescription: Hostility Score
Notes: Mean of items: 4, 5, 6, 8, 13, 16, and 29

ElementDescription: Lax Control Score
Notes: Mean of items: 2, 3, 9, 12, 20, 23, and 27

ElementDescription: Physical Control Score
Notes: Mean of items: 14, 24, 25, and 31

ElementDescription: Broadband Positive Parenting Score
Notes: Mean of items: Proactive Parenting Score, Positive Reinforcement Score, Warmth Score, and Supportiveness Score

ElementDescription: Broadband Negative Parenting Score
Notes: Mean of items: Hostility Score, Lax Control Score, and Physical Control Score

ElementDescription: Timepoint
Notes: 1 = Screening; 2 = Baseline; 3 = Mid-way; 4 = One Month; 5 = Three Months; 6 = Final
